undary between himself and the world.\n\n\"The relay,\" Kain said.\n\n\"The relay's coherence signature is oriented toward the eastern corridor. When the QSA decommissioned the site, they closed the entanglement connection but did not zero the field orientation. The orientation preserved itself.\" The voice arrived from the correct position — two metres forward and to the right, Hayden's actual location, the drift absent for the first time since the stairwell. The confined space was doing something to the acoustic refraction: the voice had nowhere to go and was arriving directly. \"The eastern corridor runs beneath Alfred Hospital's sublevel infrastructure. The relay's orientation is a compass bearing.\"\n\nThe relay was pointing toward the Sphere.\n\nThirty-one years of preserved field orientation, the ghost of an entanglement connection that had been cut but not erased, still aimed at the quantum architecture it had been calibrated to serve.\n\nThe ninth coordinate: *22-Lambda-6. Coherence Offset: 0.061.*\n\nThe ninth coordinate arrived without delay.\n\nThe primary pathway was managing. The redundancy was managing. The buffer was consuming its remaining 19% at the rate of three ICS points per hour and the relay's ambient coherence was adding a measurable load on top of that and the estimate revised downward: ICS 51\\.\n\nEleven points of margin.\n\nKain looked at the dark where the relay was and thought about Martina Solis in the Threshold facility, not retired, sequestered, her personal effects manifest logged without her journals because Emily had taken the journals four months before the sequestration was filed, and the sequestration was filed as retirement in the operational briefing because the word *retirement* belonged to the QSA's standard vocabulary and *sequestration* belonged to Article 7 and Article 7 was Tier 4 restricted and the recruit did not have Tier 4 clearance when the briefing was prepared and so the word that appeared in the briefing was the