          "text": "*The document currently under review pertains to a carrier designated CONV-PQ-GEN-549/KAIN-D, currently at 11 operational deployments.*\n\n*Your specific TUBA1A-PQ variant produces a resonance signal 340% cleaner than the median carrier signal. The Sphere's coherence structure, read through your architecture, produces data that no other carrier in the registry can match at equivalent resolution.*\n\n*Projected deployment 12 is scheduled.*\n\nHe read it again.\n\nNot because the meaning required repetition. Because the meaning required the specific, physical duration of a second reading — the time it took for the data to move from the screen through the optic nerve and into the prefrontal cortex where the microtubules were, where the *TUBA1A-PQ* variant was, where the secondary binding site was degrading at a rate the QSA had been measuring for fourteen months and had not told him about, and where the number 11 sat against the number 14 with a gap of three deployments between them and a median of four to seven months between deployment 14 and ICS collapse.\n\nHe had been deployed eleven times.\n\nEmily had the data. Emily had compiled it. Emily had amended the file fourteen months ago, which was when she had recruited him for the current operation, which was his eleventh deployment, which she had known when she recruited him was his eleventh deployment, which meant she had known when she recruited him that the twelfth would push his buffer efficiency below 19% and the thirteenth and fourteenth would follow in the operational sequence she had already planned.\n\nThe file's last amendment date was fourteen months ago.\n\nShe had known for fourteen months.\n\nThe terminal's cache timer ran to zero and the screen went dark.\n\nThe plant room was very quiet. The air handler had completed its cycle. The bypass switch was in its default position. The fibre connection was gone and the terminal was dark and the Fitzroy Node was offline and the QSA's thermal