          "text": "The laughing woman.\n\nThe specific, high, uncontrolled laugh — present in the corridor at Alfred, directional, occupying a physical position in space rather than arriving from behind his eyes. Not a hallucination. Not a symptom of damage. A residue of the Sphere's resonance, surfacing through the pathways the entanglement had opened, carrying a fragment of what the Sphere had been touching when his architecture was inside it.\n\nHe had filed it under *fragmentation* for eleven months.\n\nHe had been filing the wrong category.\n\nThe second air handler cycle arrived. He held the bypass switch and let his eyes close for four seconds.",
